<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,714,1819]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,317,1111,1135]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wagler, 1824" authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1824" box="[326,568,1111,1134]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Stenostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signatum">
<emphasis box="[326,568,1111,1134]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Stenostoma signatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jan" box="[786,907,1110,1134]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Jan, G. (1861) Note sulla famiglia dei tiflopidi sui lori generi e sulle specie del genere Stenostoma. Archivio Per La Zoologia, L'Anatomia e La Fisiologia, Genova, 1, 178 - 199." type="journal article" year="1861">
Jan (
<number box="[842,900,1110,1134]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1861.0">1861</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
through a specimen of unknown provenance. Later the 
<typeStatus box="[263,361,1146,1170]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
was illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jan" box="[584,857,1146,1170]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Jan, G. (1861) Note sulla famiglia dei tiflopidi sui lori generi e sulle specie del genere Stenostoma. Archivio Per La Zoologia, L'Anatomia e La Fisiologia, Genova, 1, 178 - 199." type="journal article" year="1861">
Jan and Sordelli (
<number box="[788,848,1146,1170]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1861.0">1861</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn" box="[870,1017,1146,1170]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Hahn, D. E. (1979) The identity of the blind snake Stenostoma signatum Jan, 1861 (Serpentes: Leptotyphlopidae). Herpetologica, 35, 57 - 60." type="journal article" year="1979">
Hahn (
<number box="[949,1009,1146,1170]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, based on the data from 
<bibRefCitation author="Jan" box="[1307,1432,1146,1170]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Jan, G. (1861) Note sulla famiglia dei tiflopidi sui lori generi e sulle specie del genere Stenostoma. Archivio Per La Zoologia, L'Anatomia e La Fisiologia, Genova, 1, 178 - 199." type="journal article" year="1861">
Jan (
<number box="[1363,1423,1146,1170]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1861.0">1861</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, pointed out that this specimen was purchased by the Muséum National d’histoire Naturalle of Paris in 
<number box="[1330,1386,1182,1206]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1858.0">1858</number>
and originally labelled as “ 
<collectingCountry box="[408,553,1218,1242]" name="Madagascar" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
?”. Because there are no Leptotyphlopid record’s to 
<collectingCountry box="[1142,1279,1218,1242]" name="Madagascar" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn" box="[1292,1436,1218,1242]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Hahn, D. E. (1979) The identity of the blind snake Stenostoma signatum Jan, 1861 (Serpentes: Leptotyphlopidae). Herpetologica, 35, 57 - 60." type="journal article" year="1979">
Hahn (
<number box="[1369,1427,1218,1242]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
argued that the label was in error. 
<taxonomicName box="[548,848,1254,1278]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Leptotyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis box="[548,848,1254,1278]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Leptotyphlops amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Orejas-Miranda" box="[1064,1325,1254,1278]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Orejas-Miranda, B. R. (1969) Tres nuevos leptotyphlops (Reptilia: Serpentes). Comunicaciones Zoologicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo, 10, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1969">
Orejas-Miranda (
<number box="[1259,1317,1254,1278]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1969.0">1969</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
based on five specimens from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[566,681,1290,1314]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and one without specific provenance, possibly from Amazon Rainforest of 
<collectingCountry box="[305,400,1326,1350]" name="Ecuador" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Orejas-Miranda" box="[411,670,1326,1350]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Orejas-Miranda, B. R. (1969) Tres nuevos leptotyphlops (Reptilia: Serpentes). Comunicaciones Zoologicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo, 10, 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1969">
Orejas-Miranda (
<number box="[604,662,1326,1350]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1969.0">1969</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
cited that the 
<typeStatus box="[830,926,1327,1351]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">paratype</typeStatus>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" box="[941,1014,1326,1350]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">ANSP</collectionCode>
<number box="[1021,1079,1326,1350]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="3290.0">3290</number>
) from Ecuadorian Amazon was from the Orton collection. However 
<bibRefCitation author="Cope" box="[581,719,1362,1386]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Cope, E. D. (1876) Report on the reptiles brought by professor James Orton from the middle and upper Amazon and western Peru. Journal of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 2, 159 - 183." type="journal article" year="1876">
Cope (
<number box="[659,719,1362,1386]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1876.0">1876</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cope" box="[735,792,1362,1386]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Cope, E. D. (1877) Synopsis of the cold blooded vertebrata, procured by prof. James Orton during his exploration of Peru. Proceedings of the American Philosophical Society, 17, 33 - 49." type="journal article" year="1877">
<number box="[735,792,1362,1386]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1877.0">1877</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) did not mention any specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1212,1371,1363,1387]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Leptotyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1212,1371,1363,1387]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Leptotyphlops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,244,1398,1422]" name="Ecuador" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[298,349,1399,1422]" name="Peru" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Peru</collectingCountry>
collected by the Orton expedition. The Orton expedition was divided in two parts, one ascending the Orinoco River and the other one through the Amazon basin. Thus, it seems that this specimen was collected by the first part while in 
<collectingCountry box="[393,508,1470,1494]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and not by the second in the Amazon (
<bibRefCitation author="Cisneros-Heredia" box="[945,1211,1470,1494]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Cisneros-Heredia, D. F. (2008) Reptilia, Squamata, Leptotyphlopidae, Leptotyphlops, Ecuador: Re-evaluation of the species cited for the country. Check List, 4, 178 - 181." type="journal article" year="2008">
Cisneros-Heredia 
<number box="[1150,1211,1470,1494]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,714,1819]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn" box="[201,344,1506,1530]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Hahn, D. E. (1979) The identity of the blind snake Stenostoma signatum Jan, 1861 (Serpentes: Leptotyphlopidae). Herpetologica, 35, 57 - 60." type="journal article" year="1979">
Hahn (
<number box="[278,337,1506,1530]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
examined the supposed 
<typeStatus box="[624,722,1506,1530]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagler, 1824" authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1824" box="[762,1001,1507,1531]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Stenostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signatum">
<emphasis box="[762,1001,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Stenostoma signatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[1016,1104,1506,1530]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">MNHN</collectionCode>
<number box="[1112,1172,1506,1530]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="3235.0">3235</number>
), comparing it with the 
<typeStatus box="[151,199,1543,1567]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName box="[314,614,1542,1566]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Leptotyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis box="[314,614,1542,1566]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Leptotyphlops amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn" box="[790,936,1542,1566]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Hahn, D. E. (1979) The identity of the blind snake Stenostoma signatum Jan, 1861 (Serpentes: Leptotyphlopidae). Herpetologica, 35, 57 - 60." type="journal article" year="1979">
Hahn (
<number box="[868,928,1542,1566]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[995,1093,1542,1566]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagler, 1824" authorityName="Wagler" authorityYear="1824" box="[1135,1268,1543,1566]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Stenostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signatum">
<emphasis box="[1135,1268,1543,1566]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">S. signatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is comparable with the 
<taxonomicName box="[258,424,1580,1603]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Leptotyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis box="[258,424,1580,1603]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">L. amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus box="[436,484,1579,1603]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
series in all meristic and morphometic characters and, therefore, he relegated 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Leptotyphlops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">L. amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the synonymy of the first, restricting the 
<typeStatus box="[776,824,1615,1639]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
locality to northern region of Amazonia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,714,1819]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Despite few known specimens and uncertain distribution there are characteristics figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jan" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Jan, G. (1861) Note sulla famiglia dei tiflopidi sui lori generi e sulle specie del genere Stenostoma. Archivio Per La Zoologia, L'Anatomia e La Fisiologia, Genova, 1, 178 - 199." type="journal article" year="1861">
Jan and Sordelli (
<number box="[159,217,1686,1710]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1861.0">1861</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Hahn" box="[287,433,1686,1710]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refString="Hahn, D. E. (1979) The identity of the blind snake Stenostoma signatum Jan, 1861 (Serpentes: Leptotyphlopidae). Herpetologica, 35, 57 - 60." type="journal article" year="1979">
Hahn (
<number box="[367,425,1686,1710]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="1979.0">1979</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
that apparently diagnose 
<taxonomicName box="[736,853,1687,1711]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Epictia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis box="[736,853,1687,1711]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. signata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from sympatric congeners (e.g., uniformly brown dorsum except for snout and last subcaudal scale white pigmented combined with higher number of middorsal scales and elongate first supralabial). On the basis of such characteristics we identified the specimen 
<collectionCode box="[1283,1342,1758,1782]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/23qr-v2gj" name="Instituto Biologico de Sao Paulo" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">IBSP</collectionCode>
<number box="[1350,1406,1758,1782]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" value="7204.0">7204</number>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[151,265,1796,1819]" class="Reptilia" family="Leptotyphlopidae" genus="Epictia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signata">
<emphasis box="[151,265,1796,1819]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">E. signata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is first specimen recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[711,821,1794,1818]" name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and the eighth known of the species.
</paragraph>
